
[1]summarily

   SUM'MARILY, adv. [from summary.] In a summary manner; briefly;
   concisely; in a narrow compass or in few words. The Lord's prayer
   teaches us summarily the things we are to ask for.

   1. In a short way or method.

   When the parties proceed summarily, and they choose the ordinary way of
   proceeding, the cause is made plenary.
